##### What is the difference between Kiss Cut and Die Cut?



 **Kiss Cut Stickers**  
  
Kiss cut stickers are a type of sticker that is cut through the vinyl material
but not through its paper backing. This allows for the stickers to be easily
peeled off and applied to surfaces. Kiss cut stickers are often made using a
special type of cutting machine that is programmed to cut the vinyl layer to a
specific depth without cutting through the backing material.

The process of making kiss cut stickers involves first printing the desired
design onto a large sheet of vinyl. Then, a cutting machine equipped with a
special blade is used to cut the vinyl into the desired shape. The blade is
set to a specific depth, allowing it to cut the vinyl layer without cutting
through the backing material.

Kiss cut stickers are popular for a variety of uses, including branding,
marketing, and personal expression. They can be made in a wide range of sizes,
shapes, and colors, making them highly customizable. Because they are easy to
peel off and apply, kiss cut stickers are ideal for use on products,
packaging, and promotional materials. They are also commonly used for home
decor, car stickers, laptop stickers, and phone cases.

Overall, kiss cut stickers are a versatile and practical type of sticker that
offers a lot of creative potential. With their unique cutting process and
endless customization options, kiss cut stickers are a great way to add some
personality and flair to any project or product.  
  

 **Die Cut Stickers**

Die cut stickers are a type of sticker that is precisely cut into a custom
shape, rather than being a simple rectangular or square shape. This is
achieved by using a die, which is a specialized tool that is created to cut
the sticker into the desired shape with extreme precision.

The process of making die cut stickers involves first printing the desired
design onto a large sheet of vinyl. Then, a die is placed over the printed
sheet, and a special machine is used to apply pressure and cut the sticker
into the custom shape. The die can be created in almost any shape or size,
allowing for a wide range of customization options.

Die cut stickers are popular for a variety of uses, including branding,
marketing, and personal expression. They are often used for product labels,
window stickers, and promotional materials. They are also commonly used for
home decor, laptop stickers, and phone cases.

Die cut stickers offer a unique advantage over other types of stickers, as
they can be cut into any shape imaginable, making them highly customizable and
perfect for creating unique and eye-catching designs. They are also highly
durable and resistant to wear and tear, making them a great option for outdoor
use.

Overall, die cut stickers are a versatile and practical type of sticker that
offers a lot of creative potential. With their precise cutting process and
endless customization options, die cut stickers are a great way to add some
personality and flair to any project or product.





Choosing between kiss cut and die cut stickers is like choosing between two
works of art. The kiss cut is like a masterpiece that is framed and
highlighted by its border, drawing attention to its beauty and intricacy.
Meanwhile, the die cut is like a sculpture, where every detail is carefully
carved and defined to create a unique and captivating design.

Both kiss cut and die cut stickers offer endless possibilities for creativity
and customization. Whether you want a sleek and simple design or a bold and
intricate masterpiece, there is a sticker cutting method that can bring your
vision to life.

So, the next time you're looking to add some flair to your laptop, water
bottle, or any other surface, consider whether a kiss cut or die cut sticker
would be the perfect fit. Either way, you can rest assured that your sticker
will be a work of art that is sure to turn heads and leave a lasting
impression.

##### What are easy peel stickers?

Easy peel stickers mean that the inset of each individual sticker will be
partially cut to the shape of your logo / design, but not all the way through
so you can easily peel it off from the backing.

The backing material is larger than the sticker itself and light surface cuts
are made along the border of your logo / design, cutting through only the
sticker (barely "kissing" it) and keeping the backing paper intact. This
method makes for easier removal as the sticker is peeled away from the
adhesive border and the paper backing remains.

Backings are available in our standard shapes: circle, oval, rectangle and
square, but you also have the option to upgrade to a custom shape to match
your inner sticker shape.

See: Can I order multiple stickers on a sheet?
